<headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued August 21 at 11:00PM EDT until August 22 at 2:00PM EDT by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...BEACH HAZARDS STATEMENT REMAINS IN EFFECT THROUGH MONDAY
AFTERNOON...
* WHAT...High wave action, strong currents, and dangerous
swimming conditions expected. Piers will be heavily swamped by
waves.
* WHERE...In Indiana, La Porte county. In Michigan, Berrien
county.
* WHEN...Through Monday afternoon.
* IMPACTS...Strong currents can pull swimmers into deeper water
and high waves can sweep people off piers.</description>
<instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.
Do not venture out on piers.</instruction>
